Privacy Policy

Last updated: May 7, 2026

Introduction

Beat Your Streak (“the App”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the App.

Information We Collect

Beat Your Streak is designed to collect as little personal information as possible.

The App may store the following information locally on your device and through your personal iCloud account:

* Goals and habit tracking data
* Streak history and progress information
* Reminder and notification preferences
* App settings and preferences

iCloud Sync

If you enable iCloud sync, your data is stored securely in your personal iCloud account using Apple’s CloudKit services. The developer of Beat Your Streak does not have access to your private iCloud data.

Please review Apple’s privacy policies for more information about how iCloud handles your data.

Analytics and Tracking

Beat Your Streak does not use third-party advertising networks.

The App does not sell your personal data.

The App does not track you across other apps or websites.

If analytics are used in the future, they will only be used to improve the functionality and stability of the App.

Notifications

If you choose to enable reminders, the App may send local notifications on your device to help you stay consistent with your goals.

Notification preferences can be changed at any time in your device settings.

Data Security

Your data is stored securely using Apple-provided technologies and protections. While reasonable measures are taken to protect your information, no method of electronic storage is completely secure.

Children’s Privacy

Beat Your Streak is not directed toward children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

Your Rights

You may delete your data at any time by:

* Removing goals within the App
* Disabling iCloud sync
* Deleting the App from your device

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updates will be reflected by revising the “Last updated” date above.

Contact

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact the developer through the App Store listing or support contact provided with the App.
